Stirring during holding appeared to have only a minor effect on the Ti recovery values (Table 3
). Alloys produced with and without stirring during holding all exhibited Ti recoveries in the neighborhood of 98%, when held at 800°C for 30min (Table 3). The Ti recovery in the case of mechanical stirring was slightly lower, possibly due to a heavier oxidation. The microstructural features of the three alloys were also similar, with predominantly blocky aluminide particles and very fine boride particles as usual (Fig. 5
a–c).
